# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# UnstableStonks configuration. Everything works out of the box against public
# endpoints — these vars only OVERRIDE defaults or unlock optional features.
# Copy to `.env` and fill in what you need. Client vars must be prefixed VITE_.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── RPC overrides (default to each network's public RPC) ────────────────────
# VITE_RPC_ROBINHOOD=https://rpc.mainnet.chain.robinhood.com
# VITE_RPC_STABLE=https://rpc.stable.xyz
# VITE_RPC_ARC=https://rpc.testnet.arc.network

# ── Block-explorer v2 API bases (default to each chain's Blockscout) ─────────
# VITE_EXPLORER_API_STABLE=https://stablescan.xyz/api/v2
# VITE_EXPLORER_API_ARC=https://testnet.arcscan.app/api/v2

# ── Swap routing + fee collection ────────────────────────────────────────────
# The 1% treasury fee (-> 0x6E53C6288Dc2C0F957Dc1F5E7d78874c3223CC96) works on any
# chain via a plain transfer. The DEX swap leg activates per chain once you set a
# Uniswap-V2-style router address and the wrapped-native token for that chain.
# VITE_ROUTER_ROBINHOOD=0x...
# VITE_WNATIVE_ROBINHOOD=0x...
# VITE_ROUTER_STABLE=0x...
# VITE_WNATIVE_STABLE=0x...
# VITE_ROUTER_ARC=0x...
# VITE_WNATIVE_ARC=0x...

# ── X (Twitter) social crawl (server-side secrets, NOT VITE_) ────────────────
# Preferred: official X API v2 bearer token — authoritative posts + impressions.
# X_BEARER_TOKEN=
# Fallback: comma-separated Nitter instances used when no bearer token is set.
# X_NITTER_INSTANCES=https://nitter.net,https://nitter.poast.org
